Gunnar was a [[Fremmenik]] [[barbarian]] from a mountain nomadic tribe. He and his friends with families left his large tribe to find a new home.{{CiteNPC|npc=Hunding|quote=SIn time, a warrior called Gunnar took his friends and their families and left the larger tribe}}

Gunnar is known to had been leading the [[Runecrafting Crusades]] around [[Kandarin]] and [[Asgarnia]].{{CiteText|text=Display case 2|quote=A group of the more warmongering of the mountain tribe broke away, led by a warrior called Gunnar, and went on a rampage across northern Kandarin and Asgarnia to put a stop to this 'runecrafting'.}} He is also responsible for the slaugthering of the [[Imcando dwarf]]s.{{CiteText|text=Display case 2|quote=The invading Fremennik were not happy about all the spellcasting and launched many attacks, reducing the Imcando to near extinction.}}
After losing significant amount of his army, he settled west of [[Avarrocka]] near the [[River Lum]], now known as the [[Barbarian Village]]. Although initial plan was to lay low and continue attacking again soon{{CiteText|text=Display case 1|quote=The barbarian invaders were running out of steam. They were pretty much forced to make peace or be wiped out, so they agreed to settle down peacefully and make a village on the Misthalin/Asgarnia border, thinking they could lie low, well positioned to build up strength and resume their campaign later..}}, they buried their hatchet with rune-users and coexist now peacefully.{{CiteNPC|npc=Hunding|quote=Some of our young, wishing to try so-called 'civilisation' and the softness of city life, abandon the tribe and move to the cities. It is sad to see them go, but we do not prevent them; we live here in our village because we love this life - we do not force it on those whom it does not suit.}} 

Gunnar is a direct ascendent to [[Gunthor the brave]], the current chiefstein of the Barbarian Village.{{CiteNPC|npc=Hunding|quote=Our current chieftain, Gunthor the Brave, is a direct- line descendent of Gunnar.}}

